User Flow on fan application  

 

 

 

Topic Index Features  

 

To implement topic index feature we've all the requirements already present on our present system, we just need to change a bit on a business rules and on a tables. 

 

We'll use all the group flow system with small modification lets summarize all the changes  

 

  1. 1.Change the logic behind upload content to a group, because on babblr any user can upload media content, now on ignited only the creator can upload content. For this, my suggestion is to create a new route pretty similar to route that we already have but we need only change the logic rules. In the bottom of line, uploading content is sending a message to bc_message table with gid of group. 

 

  1. 2.Change the way users are added to a group, now we have invitation loop to add a user to a specific group, on ignited for my understanding user will "follow" the creater of group. 

 

  1. 3.Support topic index conversation, for supporting we need to create a new table called ti_topic_conversation where secondary is a computed key between gid and cid , cid identify media content, and primary key is user bbid for supporting message we can use same bc_messages tables but now with this new key.

Topic Upload  

This routes is responsable to upload media data to a group and should be called by a creator app.  

 

HTTP Request  

POST 

/topic/upload 

Body 

  

{ 

  "groups": ["gid_of_group"], 

  "media": {

    "timestamp": 1458604765076, 

    "type": "video/youtube", 

    "file": "youtube", 

    "owner": "youtube.com", 

    "source_bbid": "O9K5nj02999JEJze5Be8OCQv00", 

    "src": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tgF1Enrgo2g",
